      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOTANOTHA NAUGHTY (6) was one of Victoria's leading juveniles of last season, winning four races including the Group 1 Redwood Classic. Back from a spell of three-and-a-half months and has changed yards in that time but looks to be right up to the mark following two trials, winning the latest. CEE CEE IN PARIS (5) is on a quick back up but couldn't have been more impressive when spanking her rivals by nearly 51m when resuming at Menangle on Tuesday. Stronger opposition here but she is hard to knock off that performance. WHAT THE TOOTH (4) resumes for a new stable having last raced in the Vicbred Super Series four months ago but was readied with a trial win. IM DREAMING (1) hasn't raced since placing behind Gladiatrix nine months ago at Menangle but was readied with three nice trials and gets the ace draw. Include at odds.",
